WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.140 --> 00:00:01.639
The rules that keep me safe,

1
00:00:02.019 --> 00:00:03.539
even when I don't feel it yet.

2
00:00:04.389 --> 00:00:06.159
My name is Isaac Iqbal,

3
00:00:06.309 --> 00:00:08.989
and I want to tell you something about the rules you follow,

4
00:00:09.390 --> 00:00:10.180
because to you,

5
00:00:10.430 --> 00:00:11.939
they might feel like paperwork,

6
00:00:12.100 --> 00:00:13.939
policies or procedures,

7
00:00:14.270 --> 00:00:15.020
but to me,

8
00:00:15.310 --> 00:00:17.530
they are the difference between being safe

9
00:00:17.709 --> 00:00:19.649
and not being safe.

10
00:00:20.110 --> 00:00:21.790
When my brain senses danger,

11
00:00:21.989 --> 00:00:23.770
my amygdala reacts first.

12
00:00:24.100 --> 00:00:25.149
It does not wait.

13
00:00:25.329 --> 00:00:26.809
It does not check facts.

14
00:00:26.989 --> 00:00:29.549
It does not think about whether I am actually safe.

15
00:00:29.829 --> 00:00:31.260
It just tells my body

16
00:00:31.670 --> 00:00:32.450
something is wrong.

17
00:00:33.229 --> 00:00:35.610
That's why I don't always act the way you expect.

18
00:00:36.110 --> 00:00:37.590
My prefrontal cortex,

19
00:00:37.709 --> 00:00:39.209
the part that helps me think,

20
00:00:39.409 --> 00:00:40.290
make decisions,

21
00:00:40.389 --> 00:00:41.830
and control my behavior,

22
00:00:42.150 --> 00:00:44.060
goes offline when I feel threatened.

23
00:00:44.389 --> 00:00:46.450
So when I shout or shut down

24
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:47.790
or push you away,

25
00:00:48.110 --> 00:00:50.049
I am not choosing to behave that way.

26
00:00:50.310 --> 00:00:52.299
My nervous system is trying to protect me,

27
00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:54.330
and this is where your rules matter.

28
00:00:54.630 --> 00:00:57.389
The Children Act says my welfare must come first.

29
00:00:57.750 --> 00:00:59.750
That means when something doesn't feel right.

30
00:01:00.009 --> 00:01:01.630
You are not allowed to ignore it,

31
00:01:01.919 --> 00:01:03.439
even if I don't say anything,

32
00:01:03.729 --> 00:01:05.489
even if I act like I don't care,

33
00:01:05.690 --> 00:01:06.870
you still have to act.

34
00:01:07.699 --> 00:01:10.180
Working together to safeguard children means you

35
00:01:10.180 --> 00:01:11.910
don't deal with things on your own,

36
00:01:12.379 --> 00:01:13.319
because sometimes

37
00:01:13.620 --> 00:01:15.769
one adult is not enough to keep me safe.

38
00:01:16.099 --> 00:01:17.580
So you share information,

39
00:01:17.739 --> 00:01:18.879
you speak to others,

40
00:01:18.980 --> 00:01:20.800
you make sure nothing gets missed,

41
00:01:21.059 --> 00:01:22.599
even when it's uncomfortable.

42
00:01:23.099 --> 00:01:26.610
The Children's home's regulations mean I should feel safe where I live.

43
00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:28.290
Not just physically safe,

44
00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:30.160
but emotionally safe too.

45
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:32.839
That means how you speak to me matters,

46
00:01:33.099 --> 00:01:34.819
how consistent you are matters.

47
00:01:35.209 --> 00:01:35.220
Because

48
00:01:35.569 --> 00:01:37.010
my brain is always asking,

49
00:01:37.370 --> 00:01:38.349
is this place safe?

50
00:01:39.050 --> 00:01:41.419
The Human Rights Act means I matter,

51
00:01:41.730 --> 00:01:42.919
even when I am angry,

52
00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:44.790
even when I get things wrong,

53
00:01:45.129 --> 00:01:46.790
even when I push people away.

54
00:01:47.050 --> 00:01:49.589
I still have the right to be treated with dignity.

55
00:01:49.889 --> 00:01:53.839
The Equality Act means I should not be treated differently because of who I am,

56
00:01:54.330 --> 00:01:55.349
because sometimes

57
00:01:55.730 --> 00:01:57.290
people like me get labeled,

58
00:01:57.650 --> 00:01:58.660
misunderstood,

59
00:01:59.050 --> 00:02:00.879
seen as a problem instead of a person.

60
00:02:01.160 --> 00:02:02.389
The SCCIF

61
00:02:02.849 --> 00:02:04.489
the way services are inspected.

62
00:02:04.940 --> 00:02:07.489
That's how people check if I actually feel safe,

63
00:02:07.860 --> 00:02:09.520
not just if boxes are ticked,

64
00:02:09.820 --> 00:02:11.619
but if my experience is better,

65
00:02:11.940 --> 00:02:13.139
if I am calmer,

66
00:02:13.380 --> 00:02:14.880
if I am being understood.

67
00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:17.720
And then there's something else you might not think about,

68
00:02:18.699 --> 00:02:19.119
information.

69
00:02:19.539 --> 00:02:23.009
The Data Protection Act says you must handle my information properly,

70
00:02:23.300 --> 00:02:24.520
but it also means

71
00:02:24.940 --> 00:02:26.800
if something is putting me at risk,

72
00:02:27.179 --> 00:02:28.500
you need to share it,

73
00:02:28.979 --> 00:02:31.539
because silence can be dangerous for someone like me.

74
00:02:32.279 --> 00:02:33.919
When I have been hurt before,

75
00:02:34.279 --> 00:02:36.419
my brain stays on high alert.

76
00:02:36.759 --> 00:02:38.699
My body fills with cortisol.

77
00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:40.699
I become hypervigilant.

78
00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:42.360
I am always scanning,

79
00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:43.740
always checking,

80
00:02:44.029 --> 00:02:46.199
always waiting for something to go wrong.

81
00:02:46.639 --> 00:02:48.240
So even when I am safe,

82
00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:50.270
I might not feel safe.

83
00:02:50.679 --> 00:02:53.179
That's why how you follow the rules matters,

84
00:02:53.600 --> 00:02:55.979
because if you follow them without understanding me,

85
00:02:56.240 --> 00:02:57.979
I will still feel unsafe.

86
00:02:58.320 --> 00:02:59.759
But when you stay calm,

87
00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:01.279
when you are consistent.

88
00:03:01.699 --> 00:03:03.529
When you listen instead of react,

89
00:03:03.899 --> 00:03:05.929
you help my nervous system settle.

90
00:03:06.179 --> 00:03:07.889
That's called co-regulation.

91
00:03:08.139 --> 00:03:10.210
You are helping my brain learn something new.

92
00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:11.440
You are showing me

93
00:03:11.580 --> 00:03:12.960
that adults can be safe.

94
00:03:13.220 --> 00:03:15.559
My hippocampus starts to build new memories,

95
00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:16.720
not just of fear,

96
00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:17.899
but of safety,

97
00:03:18.100 --> 00:03:18.800
of trust,

98
00:03:18.979 --> 00:03:20.020
of someone staying,

99
00:03:20.139 --> 00:03:21.289
even when I struggle.

100
00:03:21.580 --> 00:03:23.190
A sad reality is this.

101
00:03:23.460 --> 00:03:25.160
You can follow every policy,

102
00:03:25.339 --> 00:03:26.380
every procedure,

103
00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:27.330
every rule,

104
00:03:27.539 --> 00:03:29.240
and I can still feel unsafe.

105
00:03:29.570 --> 00:03:32.130
But when you understand why those rules exist,

106
00:03:32.380 --> 00:03:33.919
and you apply them with care,

107
00:03:34.220 --> 00:03:35.440
something changes.

108
00:03:35.660 --> 00:03:37.539
You don't just protect me from harm,

109
00:03:37.699 --> 00:03:40.119
you help my brain come out of survival mode.

110
00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:41.759
Please understand this.

111
00:03:42.059 --> 00:03:44.820
My brain learned survival before it learned safety,

112
00:03:45.220 --> 00:03:47.119
so I need you to show me safety

113
00:03:47.550 --> 00:03:48.210
again

114
00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:49.440
and again

115
00:03:49.779 --> 00:03:50.460
and again.

116
00:03:51.059 --> 00:03:51.070
Because

117
00:03:51.449 --> 00:03:52.020
for me,

118
00:03:52.419 --> 00:03:54.119
safeguarding is not a policy,

119
00:03:54.339 --> 00:03:55.970
it's how I experience you.

120
00:03:56.300 --> 00:03:57.529
And when you get it right,

121
00:03:57.820 --> 00:03:59.149
those rules you follow

122
00:03:59.460 --> 00:04:00.679
don't just protect me,

123
00:04:00.940 --> 00:04:02.360
they help me feel safe enough

124
00:04:02.779 --> 00:04:03.740
to start healing.